So. Dear Chremes, I have done wrong, I confess it: I give in. For the present Ι make this request of you, that, in proportion as your mind. is the staider from age, the more prone to pardon, there may be found some protection for my foolishness in your indulgence.

CH. Of course as far as I am concerned I shall pardon what you did : but, Sostrata, my easy temper is a bad instructor to you in many ways. However, tell me your motive, whatever it is, for entering upon this tale.

SO. As you might expect from us women who are foolish and miserably superstitious, upon giving the child to that woman to be exposed, I draw a ring from my finger, and I order her to expose it along with the girl ; so that if she died she should not be quite without share in our property.

CH. [ironically] That was excellent! you saved yourself and her. So. This is the ring.
